Issue #9: Wario now goes to sleep! Added two new states: GOTO_SLEEP and WAKE_UP to the WarioStates-category. The length of those states is controlled by the LookComponent.
Issue #15: Moved EngineWrapper out of GameActor I've created a new superclass called "EngineController". While not really needed, it's usefull to be sure that things got made rightfully.
Disabled debug-view of colliding rects & corrected some typos
Issue #17: Make Wario turn like in the original

Fix of issue #12: Wario can now always jump the height he should The problem was that in the `if self.state == WarioStates.JUMP_STAY` part, the check weather Wario was jumping before or not to reset the frame-counter was done wrongly. If UPRIGHT_STAY changes the state, then this new state gets already appended to the self.state_stack - so if you want to check what the previous state was, you have to check self.state_stack[-2] and not [-1].

Issue #7: Improve Warios jump-mechanism to resemble more the original It's better now, but not perfect. The gravity pulls a little to much, it seems. I've create a sort of "gradient" of jump-speeds: 5 x 3 pixel/frame, 4x2ppf, 8x1ppf and 2x0 ppf. As said, not perfect, but better.
NOTE: It's not possible to do jumps that have to be possible, e.g. jump from one platform to the other.

Issue #3: Tiles now contain information about their position and size - and they're sorted in a dict. This is the dict: ({layer_id: {tile_id: tile_insta,ce}}) It's not the definite solution, but it's better.
Issue #3: The offset for get_tile_relative_to() is now in the right order.
Issue #3: World now has a dict that sorts tiles by material_group
